reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So much storage in a small space
reviews.reviewText: At first, I wasn't sure on this. Definitely only half-tighten the screws until you get it built. Then it comes together easy. This stores a LOT and looks very nice. No nicks, dings or rough spots. Has hooks for hanging things, not really using them but they would be nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It was worth it, great quality
reviews.reviewText: A really nice space saver organizer EXELlANT

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functional and stylish
reviews.reviewText: If you have a small kitchen, then this spice rack will maximize your counter space, allowing room for tall sauce bottles on the bottom and smaller spice bottles on the top. It was pretty easy to assemble, just follow the pictures and make sure you have all the tools and screws, and that the holes have been drilled in all the right places. Some holes might be slightly off, I put the screws in and aligned it with the rack parts and that helped a lot with assemblage. Overall it didn’t take too long, looks nice, functions as it should and worth its price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Missing a hole in one of the sides, where the metal bars go on the back side. Doesn’t seem to be relevant to stability so I’ll live with it. Took a star off for that. Otherwise, it’s a great little shelf!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's perfect for my coffee area
reviews.reviewText: I have a 2.5 foot kitchen counter area for my coffee, cream, sugar, tea etc and it organizes the area. Perfect.
It was so easy to build. Looks super cute. Very sturdy. Love that the legs adjust so it stays level on surface.
This was a real gem added addition to my kitchen. Keeps things handy and looks amazingly decorative in my kitchen. I love this and getting lots of compliments
This is exactly what I wanted and is exactly as pictured.

reviews.reviewTitle: Assembly can be tricky but over all it’s perfect for your coffee area set up
reviews.reviewText: Took me awhile to assemble it because some of the holes for the screws were weirdly placed and one of the metal legs seem to have an extra metal on the inside which made it hard to screw on the leg (had to “clean” the inside so the screw will go in)…but over all, it’s a really good product, actual wood and metal plus the wood it comes with seem to be laminated? So it’s easy to wipe and clean. The colour is just perfect for the coffee area set up I was aiming for. Only reason this isn’t a 5 is the assembly.Make sure to measure your counter to be sure it fits between the cup board and the counter.
Fits perfectly on my counter, just what I wanted. Was pretty easy to put together too
